    "explanation": "<p>Given circuit can be shown as below </p><p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7m7mxug/d34467d0-d5c7-43c0-b8b0-76c27a84b567/07636580-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7mxuh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7m7mxug/d34467d0-d5c7-43c0-b8b0-76c27a84b567/07636580-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7mxuh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2024 Physics - Semiconductor Devices and Logic Gates Question 3 English Explanation 1\"> </p><p>Output, $ Y=\\overline{(\\bar{A})(\\bar{B})}=\\bar{A}+\\bar{B}=A+B $ </p><p>The truth table will be</p> <style type=\"text/css\"> .tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;} .tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;   overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;} .tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;   font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;} .tg .tg-cly1{text-align:left;vertical-align:middle} .tg .tg-wa1i{font-weight:bold;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle} .tg .tg-uzvj{border-color:inherit;font-weight:bold;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle} </style> <table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 456px\"><colgroup> <col style=\"width: 152px\"> <col style=\"width: 152px\"> <col style=\"width: 152px\"> </colgroup> <tbody>   <tr>     <td class=\"tg-uzvj\">$A$</td>     <td class=\"tg-wa1i\">$B$</td>     <td class=\"tg-wa1i\">$Y=A+B$</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">0</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">0</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">0</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">0</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">1</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">1</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">1</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">0</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">1</td>   </tr>   <tr>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">1</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">1</td>     <td class=\"tg-cly1\">1</td>   </tr> </tbody> </table> <p>The corresponding input and ou put waveforms are shown below. </p><p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7m7n5hr/5c8d0566-b3e6-4a3b-bfa3-c6ac5ed68c5f/0d4bd900-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7n5hs.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7m7n5hr/5c8d0566-b3e6-4a3b-bfa3-c6ac5ed68c5f/0d4bd900-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7n5hs.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2024 Physics - Semiconductor Devices and Logic Gates Question 3 English Explanation 2\"></p>",
