    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>For an insulator, the forbidden energy gap is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "Zero "
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "1eV"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "2eV"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "5eV"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>For an insulator, E<sub>g</sub> > 3 eV, that is why electron transition from valence band to conduction band is not possible. For semiconductor E<sub>g</sub> is 0.2 eV to 0.3 eV, while for metals E<sub>g</sub> > 5 eV.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
