    "content": "<p>In the circuit shown assume the diode to be ideal. When V<sub>i</sub> increases from $$-$$2V to 6V, the change in current is (in mA)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lhye4k38/4d5bd23e-5101-4586-bf5b-cac984cfbb86/300af740-f85f-11ed-a585-812e165f6969/file-1lhye4k39.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lhye4k38/4d5bd23e-5101-4586-bf5b-cac984cfbb86/300af740-f85f-11ed-a585-812e165f6969/file-1lhye4k39.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2022 Physics - Semiconductor Devices and Logic Gates Question 7 English\"></p>",
