    "explanation": "<p>According to the given figure X is at lower potential w.r.t Y. Hence, both diodes are in reverse biasing, so, equivalent circuit can be redrawn as follows</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lhyg7mmr/7c67d59a-b395-4612-be37-ff3650e951b0/57b12320-f867-11ed-a462-b137e84afc65/file-1lhyg7moe.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lhyg7mmr/7c67d59a-b395-4612-be37-ff3650e951b0/57b12320-f867-11ed-a462-b137e84afc65/file-1lhyg7moe.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2022 Physics - Semiconductor Devices and Logic Gates Question 6 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Equivalent resistance between X and Y</p>\n<p>R<sub>eq</sub> = 8 + 2 + 6 = 16$$\\Omega$$</p>",
