  {
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A transistor is connected in common-emitter (CE) configuration. The collector supply is 8V and the voltage drop across a resistor is 500 $$\\Omega$$ in the collector circuit is 0.6 V. IF the current gain factor $$\\alpha$$ is 0.96, find the base current</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "25 $$\\mu$$A"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "50 $$\\mu$$A"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "20 $$\\mu$$A"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "35 $$\\mu$$A"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given, V<sub>CC</sub> = 8V</p>\n<p>Voltage drop, V<sub>0</sub> = $$\\Delta$$I<sub>C</sub> R<sub>L</sub> = 0.6V</p>\n<p>Load Resistor, R<sub>L</sub> = 500 $$\\Omega$$</p>\n<p>Gain factor, $$\\alpha$$ = 0.96</p>\n<p>$$\\because$$ $$\\beta  = {\\alpha  \\over {1 - \\alpha }} = {{0.96} \\over {1 - 0.96}} = 24$$</p>\n<p>Now, V<sub>0</sub> = $$\\Delta$$I<sub>C</sub> R<sub>L</sub></p>\n<p>0.6 = $$\\Delta$$I<sub>C</sub> $$\\times$$ 500</p>\n<p>$$\\Delta$$I<sub>C</sub> = $$\\frac{0.6}{500}$$ = 1.2 $$\\times$$ 10<sup>$$-$$3</sup> A</p>\n<p>Now, $$\\beta  = {{\\Delta {I_C}} \\over {\\Delta {I_B}}}$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Base current $$\\Delta {I_B} = {{\\Delta {I_C}} \\over \\beta } = {{1.2 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}} \\over {24}} = 5 \\times {10^{ - 5}}$$</p>\n<p>= 50 $$\\times$$ 10<sup>$$-$$6</sup></p>\n<p>$$\\Delta$$I<sub>B</sub> = 50 $$\\mu$$A</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
