    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The given combination of gates is shown below</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ls2ig5ja/1623d012-d729-49ea-9cb4-4263b3c6bc91/6369ca60-c09d-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2ig5jb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ls2ig5ja/1623d012-d729-49ea-9cb4-4263b3c6bc91/6369ca60-c09d-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2ig5jb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2020 Physics - Semiconductor Devices and Logic Gates Question 10 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>The output of this combination can be determined by Boolean algebra.</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Output, $$X = \\overline {\\overline A \\,.\\,\\overline B }  = \\overline{\\overline A}  + \\overline{\\overline B} $$ [Using De Morgan's theorem]</p>\n<p>$$ \\Rightarrow X = A + B$$</p>\n<p>This is the output of OR gate. Hence, the given combination of gates yield OR gate.</p>",
